cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CL

This paper is about a machine learning system that allows users to write or adapt their own operators for each problem. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests cs.LG and cs.AI as the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a functional language, Erlang, which could suggest the sub-categories of cs.SE (software engineering) and cs.PL (programming languages). Finally, the paper mentions the application of the system to structured prediction problems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CL (computational linguistics).
